.Dd @MDOCDATE@
.Dt CLOWN-STDIO-BRIDGE 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm clown-stdio-bridge
.Nd bridge a stdio MCP server to streamable-HTTP for clown-plugin-host
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Fl -command Ar cmd
.Cm --
.Op Ar args
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
wraps a JSON-RPC-over-stdio MCP server and exposes it on an ephemeral
loopback HTTP port speaking the streamable-HTTP MCP transport.
The wrapped server is spawned as a child process; its stdin and stdout
are driven by
.Nm Ap s
translator goroutines.
.Pp
.Nm
is launched by
.Xr clown-plugin-host 1
as the synthesized command for any
.Li stdioServers
entry in
.Xr clown-json 5 .
Plugin authors do not invoke
.Nm
directly; they declare a stdio MCP server in
.Pa clown.json
and clown desugars it into a
.Li httpServers
entry pointing at this binary.
The desugaring lets stdio-declared servers and native HTTP servers share
a single discovery and lifecycle path under
.Xr clown-plugin-host 1 .
.Pp
On launch
.Nm
prints the same handshake line as a native clown-plugin server (see
.Xr clown-plugin-protocol 7 ) ,
binds
.Li 127.0.0.1:0 ,
and serves
.Li GET /healthz
and
.Li {GET,POST,DELETE} /mcp .
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl -command Ar cmd
The wrapped stdio MCP server binary.
Resolved against the caller's
.Ev PATH
via
.Xr execvp 3 ;
absolute paths bypass lookup.
Required.
.It Cm --
Separator between
.Nm
flags and the wrapped command's argv.
Everything after
.Cm --
is taken verbatim as the wrapped command's arguments, including any
literal
.Cm --
tokens.
.El
.Sh PROTOCOL TRANSLATION
.Nm
implements a subset of the streamable-HTTP MCP transport sufficient to
bridge a stdio MCP server with no client-side awareness:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Li POST /mcp Pq JSON-RPC request
The body is forwarded verbatim, followed by a newline, to the wrapped
child's stdin.
.Nm
blocks the HTTP request until a JSON-RPC response with the matching
.Li id
arrives on the child's stdout, then returns it as
.Li application/json .
.It Li POST /mcp Pq JSON-RPC notification or response
The body is forwarded fire-and-forget; the HTTP layer responds with
.Li 202 Accepted
immediately.
.It Li GET /mcp
Opens a Server-Sent Events stream.
Server-initiated JSON-RPC messages from the wrapped child
.Pq i.e., lines on its stdout that have a Li method No field but no matching pending Li id
are broadcast to every active SSE subscriber as
.Li data:\& Ns Ar payload
events.
.It Li DELETE /mcp
Returns
.Li 405 Method Not Allowed .
Session termination is not supported in v1; the bridge does not assign
session IDs.
.El
.Pp
The
.Li Origin
header is restricted to loopback origins
.Pq Li 127.0.0.1 , Li ::1 , Li localhost
or absent, per the streamable-HTTP spec's DNS-rebinding mitigation.
Other origins receive
.Li 403 Forbidden .
.Sh RESOURCE LIMITS
.Nm
caps the number of pending JSON-RPC messages in each direction at a
fixed depth.
On overflow:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Sy Inbound Pq HTTP No -> child stdin
The offending HTTP request receives a JSON-RPC error response with code
.Li \-32000
and message
.Dq clown-stdio-bridge: inbound queue saturated .
The wrapped child stays alive.
.It Sy Outbound Pq child stdout No -> SSE subscriber
The oldest pending broadcast in the offending subscriber's channel is
dropped to make room.
A counter
.Pq exposed via Sy DroppedOutbound
records the cumulative drop count.
.El
.Pp
The depth is a tuning parameter and may change between minor versions.
.Sh CRASH BEHAVIOR
If the wrapped child exits unexpectedly,
.Nm
logs the exit status and itself exits non-zero.
.Xr clown-plugin-host 1 Ap s
existing failure path
.Pq Li StartReport.Failed , Fl -skip-failed
handles restart-or-abort.
.Nm
is a transport adapter, not a supervisor.
.Sh SHUTDOWN
On
.Dv SIGTERM
or
.Dv SIGINT ,
.Nm
sends
.Dv SIGTERM
to the wrapped child's process group, waits up to 5 seconds for clean
exit, then escalates to
.Dv SIGKILL .
The HTTP server is gracefully shut down on the same path.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Nm
exits
.Li 0
on a clean
.Dv SIGTERM Ns / Ns Dv SIGINT
shutdown after spawning the wrapped child successfully.
Exit status
.Li 1
indicates an error reachable before or during the wrapped child's
lifetime: missing or invalid flags, command lookup failure, network
listen failure, HTTP serve error, or unexpected child exit.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr claude-code 1 ,
.Xr clown 1 ,
.Xr clown-plugin-host 1 ,
.Xr clown-json 5 ,
.Xr clown-plugin-protocol 7
